# ecoPrimals sweetGrass Standards

## Rust Standards
- Edition 2024 (`resolver = "3"`), Rust 1.87+
- `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]` on all crate roots
- `#![warn(missing_docs)]` on library crates
- `clippy::pedantic` + `clippy::nursery` zero warnings
- `unwrap_used` and `expect_used` denied in production code (use `#[expect(...)]` in tests)
- `thiserror` for all error types, `Result<T, E>` everywhere

## Code Size & Style
- No files > 1000 lines — split into modules
- No TODO/FIXME/HACK in committed code — track in handoffs
- No commented-out code
- Semantic method naming: `{domain}.{operation}` (e.g. `braid.create`, `health.check`)

## Architecture
- JSON-RPC 2.0 mandatory, tarpc for high-performance paths
- Pure Rust — no gRPC, no protobuf, no OpenSSL, no reqwest (enforced via `deny.toml`)
- Primal code has self-knowledge only; discovers other primals at runtime via capabilities
- No hardcoded primal names or addresses — use `Capability` enum for discovery
- Mocks isolated to `#[cfg(any(test, feature = "test"))]`

## Licensing
- AGPL-3.0-only (scyBorg triple-copyleft)
- `// SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-only` on every `.rs` file
- `// Copyright (C) 2024–2026 ecoPrimals Project` on line 2

## Testing
- `cargo test --all-features` zero failures
- Target 90%+ line coverage (llvm-cov)
- Property-based testing with `proptest` for data structures

